uicide, and from the typology of hunger and starvation to the technology of crime and punishment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aChinese fictionxHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aChinese fictionxHistory and criticismxTaiwan. 0aChinese fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aChinese fictionzTaiwanxHistory and criticism. 0aViolence in literature. 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh  a20th century.  aancient china.  aasia scholars.  abrutal history.  achina.  achinese history.  achinese violence.  acrime and punishment.  acultural violence.  adecapitation.  adiscussion books.  aenlightenment.  aethnic issues.  agender issues.  ageopolitical change.  ahistorians.  ahistorical.  ahistory of violence.  aliterary criticism.  aliterary critics.  aliterary landscape.  amodernity.  amonstrous history.  anonfiction.  apolitics.  arationality.  arepresentation.  astudents and teachers.  asuicide.  ataowu.  atextbooks.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093724640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520937246423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520937246/original  a978-3-11-064977-2  Asian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagec2000d2014  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles